<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=17426&amp;p=223428#p223428"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: InfinitROB]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=17426&amp;p=223428#p223428"><![CDATA[
Completed features list:<br /><br />InfinitROB uses a custom circuit board and code based on the Arduino Pro Micro to enable the following features:<br />- 3 Motor PWM Control (on-board electronics support up to 4)<br />- Turn and Height Sensors (original equipment)<br />- RGB LED pixel strip control (WS2812B or similar, see FastLED library for compatible pixels).<br />- NES Controller interface for direct gamepad control (using NESpad library)<br />- Servo control (such as HXT500)<br />- 8 expansion buttons (CD4021BE shift register - additional buttons possible with daisy-chained shift registers)<br />- TX/RX serial communication (with turn and height sensors on expansion button shift register)<br />- Additional input/output pin for items such as photosensors, piezos, etc. <br />- Gyromite support possible on modern monitor (beta feature)<br />- HID Device emulation (keyboard/mouse)<br />- USB MIDI Support (with MIDI library)<br />- Reprogrammability<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=8545">InfinitR</a> — Mon Aug 13, 2018 11:13 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
